              </li>
            </ul>
          </p>
        </li>
      </ol>
    </p>
  </statement>
  <hint permid="Xon">
    <p permid="RNw">
      <ol label="a." permid="bYg">
        <li permid="oWs">
          <p permid="EPk">
            Remember that a function is increasing on an interval if and only if its first derivative is positive on the interval.
          </p>
        </li>

        <li permid="VdB">
          <p permid="kWt">
            See (a).
          </p>
        </li>

        <li permid="BkK">
          <p permid="RdC">
            Remember that the first derivative of a function measures its instantaneous rate of change.
          </p>
        </li>

        <li permid="hrT">
          <p permid="xkL">
            Think about how <m>s''(t) = [s'(t)]'</m>.
          </p>
        </li>

        <li permid="Nzc">
          <p permid="drU">
            Be very careful with your letters:
            <m>s</m>, <m>v</m>, and <m>a</m>.
          </p>
        </li>
